TNK-BP Board Approves Talks on Brazil Fields, Hayward Steps Down

-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 
2011-09-26T06:50:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/tnk-bp-board-approves-talks-on-brazil-fields-hayward-steps-down.html
TNK-BP Ltd.’s board approved
further talks on acquiring blocks in  Brazil ’s Solimoes basin,
the Russian oil venture, owned 50-50 by  BP Plc (BP/)  and a group of
billionaires, said today in an e-mailed statement.  The board approved an additional dividend of $1.25
billlion, according to the statement.  Former BP Chief Executive Officer  Tony Hayward  stepped down
from the board, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow at 
